  "title": "Upgrades Boost Database Market (data mining and SGI-IBM rivalry)",
  "description": "InformationWeek (Issue 575) reporting Silicon Graphics' data-mining entry against IBM at DB Expo, San Francisco. Context: Sybase and Informix warned on Q1 1996 revenue, triggering double-digit share-price declines (Informix -28% in one day). Kastner (Aberdeen Group analyst) calls the sell-off 'a wrong conclusion' from individual situations \u2014 argues database leaders remain solid double-digit growers. Oracle then reassured analysts, sparking database-stock rebound.",
